    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Hillary's War</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>June 3 article on Sen Hillary Rodham Clinton's record on Iraq prompts letters from Dale E Hunt, Stephen Paine, Daniel A Simon, Lynn Rice, Charles Hamlin and Daniel Bauman</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Jeff Gerth and Don Van Natta Jr. resurrected first-class political journalism in their article (June 3). No character assassination, no political muckraking, no hidden agenda, just documented and verifiable statements regarding Senator Clinton and specifically her Senate voting record concerning United States military operations in Iraq. In this matter, the record clearly indicates that she did not ask herself the pertinent question about the best interests of this country, only what was best -- or the least damaging -- for her political ambitions. An even more pertinent question is how this mind-set would influence her decisions as president, a question voters should seriously consider, given that she may be the Democratic presidential candidate in 2008.</p>
      </block>
